<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910912-0095</DOCNO><DOCID>910912-0095.</DOCID><HL>   Sun Co. to Consolidate Staffs</HL><DATE>09/12/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11</SO><CO>   SUN</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)</MS><IN>OIL-INTEGRATED MAJORS (OIL)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><NS>PETROLEUM MARKET (PET)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)PENNSYLVANIA (PA)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   RADNOR, Pa. -- Sun Co. said it will consolidate thecompany's corporate staff at Radnor and the Sun Refining andamp;Marketing Co. unit into one organization by next April.   The new organization, Sun Co. Inc., will be based in Sun'sPhiladelphia offices. The company said its real-estatesubsidiary, Radnor Corp., will remain in Radnor. Sun alsowill retain its Sunbrook conference center there.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>